<br>
I met this guy at work. Who is also married. We got along famously, right off the bat. So we all started to hang out, as couples, going to parties, camping and what not. No biggie, it was cool. A new friend.<br>
<br>
Then the flirting started. First in e-mail, then in person. And he was everything that I kinda was missing in my married life. Yes, the passion had died some after 5 years, and it was nice to feel desired again by a very intelligent, smooth, witty..and let's face it, downright sexy man...and not the usual stupid bar-type a-hole. And come on! Flirting is fun! It's a nice witty banter...who can play the best game. <br>
<br>
So it got to the point where we both said to each other 'listen, this is all in fun, right? I mean, we're both happily married, and cannot go anywhere.' Which was fine and good. Boundaries were drawn, let the games continue.<br>
<br>
And my husband would go away for a weekend, and my new friend and I would go out to coffee or a party and just hang out. Often to witness the sun come up as we talked about Marx and Engles, art, religion, whatnot. I ADORE those nights. My husband and I never really did that...he conks out usually by 1 or so. <br>
<br>
So I went into work yesterday, and he wasn't there. And it bothered me. I felt...empty.<br>
<br>
Today we had an e-mail session of how much we enjoy each others company...<br>
<br>
So I went home and sat there and thought. And here is my conclusion. When I wake up in the morning, I can't wait to get to work to see him. When I get there, I can't wait to get to my Outlook. When he looks at me, I melt. I feel like I'm being torn in two, like I'm suffocating. When he sits across from me and talks, i feel like i'll die if he doesn't reach over and touch me, my leg, my arm, toussle my hair, whatever...<br>
<br>
I'm dying over here. I love my husband to death...I meant all the vows I said and promises whispered and my heart breaks to think of hurting him. But my Friend makes me feel so alive...so vibrant...so sexy and wanted and smart and interesting. I tell myself that I have a crush, and that it'll pass....<br>
<br>
I don't know what to do. Helllllllp! And thanks.... <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.villagephotos.com/p/2003-7/266009/Katriani.jpg" style="height:289;width:225;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syllestraefv>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3662<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/9/03 7:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1906.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Ok, So I need advice...(long)</span><hr size=1> If you do still love your husband... why not be honest with him?<br>
<br>
Tell him that you're not getting everything that you need out of your marriage and if things continue the way they are there's the possibility you won't be around in the long run.<br>
<br>
Ask him if he'd be willing to set aside some time to go out on dates w/ you, and treat them as actual dates.<br>
<br>
All the time you're spending out with this guy wishing your home life was like that could just as easily be spent with your husband making your home life like that.<br>
<br>
But yeah, anyways, definately go out on dates.  You won't reconnect like that in front of the TV with dirty dishes waitin.  Pretend company is in town and you have to think up some fun things to do, and then go do them.  The zoo, botanical gardens, just wander around downtown, whatever.<br>
<br>
If your husband loves you back I imagine he'd make the time available.<br>
<br>
