<br>
There's nothing wrong with you for wanting some of that back.  But take a look at yourself.  I'd also wager that you have stopped doing many things that made him initially so attracted to you in the first place.<br>
<br>
Maybe I am out of line by saying that, but it is what I observe in most other relationships.  <br>
<br>
I hope you will take the fact that this new guy is sexy completely out of the equation though.<br>
<br>
Ok, so.  My advice.  I second that you need to stop seeing this man outside of work.  To say that any human is immune to temptation is folly.  People can be subject to temptation, and be partially innocent for their ensuing actions.  HOWEVER.  You have COMPLETE control over whether or not the situations conductive to that temptation ever occur.  Bad things are happening with this guy, get away from him.  If you both love your respective spouse, and continue to see eachother, you'll end up hurting 4 people.<br>
